# Day 31: Building the Skeleton with HTML5

**Date:** [Insert Date]

**Topics Covered:**
1. HTML Document Structure (`<html>`, `<head>`, `<body>`).
2. Semantic Tags (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<footer>`).
3. Block vs Inline Elements (`<div>` vs `<span>`).
4. Essential tags: Headings, Paragraphs, Lists.

**Learning Summary:**
Today I shifted gears from Backend logic to Frontend structure. I learned that HTML is not a programming language but a markup language. I focused on "Semantic HTML"â€”using tags that describe meaning (like using `<nav>` for menus instead of just `<div>`). This is important for SEO and accessibility.

**Code Snippet:**
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>My First Webpage</title>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Developer Diary</h1>
        <nav>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="#home">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="#about">About</a></li>
            </ul>
        </nav>
    </header>
    
    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>Day 31 Progress</h2>
            <p>I learned about the <strong>DOM</strong> structure today.</p>
        </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2026 Developer Journey</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
